<br>
From where my guild and our raiding stands, if you are there you are there for 2 reasons<br>
<br>
1) To get your character an upgrade<br>
<br>
2) To provide your help in getting others upgrades<br>
<br>
That is why I like raiding as it stands right now. It divides people who are willing to be part of something for the greater good from people who are mainly concerned with their own personal advancement. I have been on more raids than I can count where I have died more than 3 times and not even walked away with PP loot. But I was there because I wanted to help, not because I wanted something.<br>
<br>
Add the ability to share xp to raids and people will come for the xp and loot, not to help others.<br>
<br>
Fair Enough Pyne. I guess my post was a semi-flame too. <br>
